IPL's highest wicket-taker Lasith Malinga and highest run scorer Chris Gayle went unsold on day one of the IPL 2018 auction in Bengaluru.They would be produced for the auction tomorrow as well.However, certain critics say that there's a possibility that they both go unsold and even could not play the 2018 IPL.Gayle had set his base price at INR 2 crore (USD 312,500 approx) and Malinga at INR 1 crore (USD 156,000 approx), numbers that were breached several times in the sale of other players during the day.